ProjectileRangeFormula

The Projectile Range Formula

The distance, $R$, that a projectile that is launched from the ground will travel before it hits the ground again depends on the launch speed, $v_{0}$, the angle between the initial velocity of the projectile and the ground, $\theta$, and the acceleration due to gravity, $g$.

R = \frac{v_{0}^{2} \sin (2 \theta)}{g}

where:

R [var. scal. Range, L, m] is the horizontal distance that the projectile will travel
v_{0} [var. scal. InitialSpeed, L T^{-1}, m s^{-1}] is the launch speed of the projectile
\theta [var. scal. LaunchAngle] is the angle between the initial velocity of the projectile and the ground
g [const. scal. AccelerationDueToGravity, L T^{-2}, m s^{-2}] is the acceleration due to gravity


